 relatives.</p>\n</div>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/helpsheets/hs340.pdf\" title=\"Help with tax relief on loans helpsheet, PDF, 107KB\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Tax relief on loans helpsheet’ (PDF, 107KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Living accommodation</h2>\n<p>If you (or one of your relatives) is living in accommodation provided by your employer you may pay tax. </p>\n\n<p>How the tax is worked out depends on whether the accommodation cost more than £75,000.</p>\n\n<p>You may not pay tax if you get the accommodation so you can do your job, or do your job better (eg agricultural workers living on farms).</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/helpsheets/hs202.pdf\" title=\"Living accommodation helpsheet, PDF, 108KB\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Living accommodation helpsheet’ (PDF, 108KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Medical insurance</h2>\n<p>You usually pay tax on the cost of the insurance premiums if your employer pays for your medical insurance.</p>\n\n<p>You can get some tax-free health benefits from your employer, eg:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>medical insurance when you&rsquo;re working abroad</li>\n  <li>annual check-ups </li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Find out how your employer <a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/paye/exb/a-z/a/index.htm\" title=\"A-Z of taxable company benefits\" rel=\"external\">works out what tax to take</a> for expenses and benefits you get.</p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tax-company-benefits/taxfree-company-benefits","slug":"taxfree-company-benefits","order":4,"title":"Tax-free company benefits","body":"<p>You can get some company benefits tax-free, including:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>meals in a staff canteen </li>\n  <li>hot drinks and water at work</li>\n  <li>a mobile phone </li>\n  <li>workplace parking </li>\n  <li>Christmas parties</li>\n  <li>childcare</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tax-company-benefits/national-insurance-on-company-benefits","slug":"national-insurance-on-company-benefits","order":5,"title":"National Insurance on company benefits","body":"<p>You don&rsquo;t usually have to pay National Insurance on benefits you get from your job if they&rsquo;re not paid in cash. </p>\n\n<p>Your employer will pay National Insurance contributions on them instead.</p>\n\n<p>But if the benefits you get are cash or treated like cash your employer will take extra National Insurance from your wages. </p>\n\n<p>For example, if your employer gives you a gift that you could sell instead of keep, you will pay National Insurance on the value of the the gift if you sold it.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Check if your employeer needs to take National Insurance contributions for <a href=\"http://www.hmrc.gov.uk/paye/exb/a-z/a/index.htm\" title=\"A-Z of taxable company benefits\" rel=\"external\">your type of company benefit.</a></p>\n</div>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/tax-company-benefits/paperwork-and-reporting-changes-to-your-company-benefits","slug":"paperwork-and-reporting-changes-to-your-company-benefits","order":6,"title":"Paperwork and reporting changes to your company benefits","body":"<p>At the end of each tax year, your employer will give you details of the company benefits that they&rsquo;ve told HM Revenue &amp; Customs (<abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr>) about. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You must keep these details for two years after the tax year they relate to.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>If you start or stop getting benefits from work</h2>\n\n<p>You must tell <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> about any benefits you or your family start or stop getting from work - even if your employer has already taken Income Tax and National Insurance for them.</p>\n\n<p>Call <abbr title=\"HM Revenue &amp; Customs\">HMRC</abbr> to let them know.</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abb